mechanisms.body:
The Kepler manifold captures **five broad, mutually-reinforcing modalities** that no competitor has jointly instrumented at fleet scale [S-513]:

- kinematic — a 400 Hz 6-axis IMU reading road roughness, grip torque, and crash signatures;
- environmental — particulate, VOC, and humidity sensing that builds air-quality maps street-by-street;
- acoustic — a MEMS array capturing failing-relay and bearing signatures for predictive maintenance;
- positional — dual-band GNSS resolving position to sub-metre, lane-level rather than road-level;
- electrical — battery-cell impedance and charger telemetry carried by the KN-2.

The uniqueness is **not any single stream** — competitors buy IMUs and GNSS too, and can match Kepler on any one axis. It is the **joint distribution**: only Kepler observes all five from the same calibrated node, time-aligned, across the same 42-city fleet [S-077]. That co-observation is the raw material breadth is made of, and it is why the sample cannot be reconstructed after the fact by anyone lacking the placed hardware — the modalities correlate node-by-node, and the correlations are the asset, not the streams.
